pr_review_comment_body:
Instead of calling `find_mountpoint()` on each property. Add a private attribute for caching values.

Something like:

```python
def __init__(self, path):
    self._attrs = None
    self.path = path
    super(MountPoint, self).__init__()

def _get_attrs(self):
    if self._attrs is None:
        self._attrs = self.get_mountpoint()
    return self._attrs

@property
def device(self):
   return self._get_attrs()["device"]
```

@rbcarson I suppose it depends on how RFC-pedantic you want to be- from [7235](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7235#section-3.1): 
```The "Authorization" header field allows a user agent to authenticate itself with an origin server -- usually, but not necessarily, after receiving a 401 (Unauthorized) response.``` 
I'm not sure what other use cases people use this auth package for, but I know in my case, preemptive auth is a huge perf win.

This whole section could be
```python
try:
    credObj.renew()
except CredentialRenewalError:
    return False
else:
    return True
```
since `renew()` will never return a value any more.
